==English==

===Etymology===
A loan word from {{G.}}, possibly a neologism in the German-language Wikipedia.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{wjargon}} A deliberately fictitious entry in an encyclopedia or dictionary, which is intended to be more or less quickly recognized as false by the reader. If expected to be easily identified it might be called an [[Easter egg]] in English (from computer games: a hidden surprise). Subtly hidden ones might be a method of [[branding]] the [[intellectual property]] so it can be recognized if copied.